<image 1>What is this?

A. Adrenergic synapse
B. Cholinergic synapse
C. Peripheral synapse
D. Autonomic synapse

The image depicts an adrenergic synapse, which is characterized by the presence of norepinephrine (NE) as the neurotransmitter, the presence of the enzyme PNMT (Phenylethanolamine N-Methyltransferase), and the involvement of G-proteins (α2 and β1/β2) in the postsynaptic cell. Therefore, the correct answer is A.
